## Building Sets from Other Sets

Now we have the machinery necessary to describe how to build sets from other
sets.
::


[\subset:of{B}]
Describes: A
when: 'B is \set'
satisfies:
. forAll: a
  where: 'a [.in.]: A'
  then: 'a [.in.]: B'
Documented:
. called: "subset of $B?$"
------------------------------------------
Id: "c20a5eaa-5c1b-448c-9678-cdc53a7dabcf"


[\superset:of{B}]
Describes: A
when: 'B is \set'
satisfies:
. forAll: b
  where: 'b [.in.]: B'
  then: 'b [.in.]: A'
Documented:
